The paper deals with selection lemmas in discrete geometry, which is a subfield of computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial and probabilistic arguments, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with geometric range searching, which is a topic in cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MS (Mathematical Software).
